LuaScript:
function onload()
    allObjects = getAllObjects()
    setupButton = nil
    tileBag = nil
    firstBag = nil
    secondBag = nil
    for i, v in ipairs(allObjects) do
        if v.hasTag("setupbutton") then
            setupButton = v
        end
        if v.hasTag("tilebag") then
            tileBag = v
        end
        if v.hasTag("firstbag") then
            firstBag = v
        end
        if v.hasTag("secondbag") then
            secondBag = v
        end
    end
    setupUI()
end

function setupUI()
    setupButton.setColorTint({1,1,1,1})
    local setupParams = {
        click_function = "setupGame",
        function_owner = Global,
        label          = "START\nGAME",
        position       = {0, 1, 0},
        rotation       = {0, 180, 0},
        width          = 500,
        height         = 500,
        font_size      = 150,
        color          = {1, 1, 1},
        font_color     = {0.2, 0.2, 0.2},
    }
    setupButton.createButton(setupParams)
end

function setupGame()
    Wait.time(function() dealObjects(tileBag, 32.72, 3) end, 0.1, 11)
    Wait.time(function() dealObjects(firstBag, 32.72, 2.25) end, 0.1, 11)
    Wait.time(function() dealObjects(secondBag, 32.72, 2) end, 0.1, 11)
    Wait.time(function() setupButton.destruct() tileBag.destruct() firstBag.destruct() secondBag.destruct() end, 1.5, 1)
end

function dealObjects(target, rotationOffset, positionOffset)
    local buttonPosition = Vector(setupButton.getPosition())
    local buttonRotation = Vector(setupButton.getRotation())
    local params = {
        position = setupButton.positionToWorld(Vector(0,0,positionOffset))
    }
    local takenObject = target.takeObject(params)
    takenObject.setLock(true)
    takenObject.setRotation(buttonRotation)

    setupButton.setRotation(Vector(0,buttonRotation.y + rotationOffset, 0))
end
